      {
        "id": 4161743,
        "name": "Luis Manuel Debuque Monreal Ermita\u00f1o",
        "username": "LMD_Ermitano",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/lmd_ermitano/{size}/77101_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-09-26T16:04:10.325Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I haven\u2019t read the subject article since I see no link; but, just from my (not so) recent personal experience with Bonneau du Martray Corton Charlemagne, particularly the 2009 vintage, I bought 3 bottles to try out sometime in late 2020 and opened them in mid 2021 (so barely 11 years from harvest), and 1 of the 3 was obviously prematurely oxidised. A minuscule sampling, I know; but, just saying\u2026.</p>",
